The paper deals with a communication system and its performance analysis, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The system involves bidirectional cooperation between two receivers, which is a common topic in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the influence of spectral resources, which is a topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The simulation results mentioned in the paper suggest the use of signal processing techniques, which is a topic in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the way of recombining signals, which is a topic in the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
